CHATSESSION_MESSAGE_RECEIVED

public static final int CHATSESSION_MESSAGE_RECEIVED
Event code, indicating that a message was received, without any problems. The message content (and the sender's ID) can be obtained by casting the event to ChatSessionMessageEvent.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

CHATSESSION_OFFLINE_MESSAGE_RECEIVED

public static final int CHATSESSION_OFFLINE_MESSAGE_RECEIVED
Event code, indicating that an offline message was received. This means that the message was received after we'd logged out of a previous session, and is now being received because we have established a new session. The message content (and the sender's ID) can be obtained by casting the event to ChatSessionMessageEvent.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

CHATSESSION_MESSAGE_COMPOSING

public static final int CHATSESSION_MESSAGE_COMPOSING
Event code, indicating that a message is currently being composed by the remote user. Such notifications are used to show that the remote user is actually active. Use the info field to get the exact state being indicated.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

CHATSESSION_REPORT_SUCCESS

public static final int CHATSESSION_REPORT_SUCCESS
